{"id":14880803,"mediaExerciseId":"2c7bc9d4-8b5d-43b0-8c62-37d3bb4d9b74","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612275,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":85,"solutions":[{"id":5958586,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the debt-equity ratio for Jack Corp.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/1fe9d4e657d3435c8bd3f5452548317d/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/1fe9d4e657d3435c8bd3f5452548317d/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define DuPont Identity.\n\n**DuPont Identity** is an expression that shows the Return on Equity (ROE) of a company.\n\nThe formula is denoted as follows:\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{ROE}& =\n \\text{Profit Margin} \\times\\text{Asset Turnover} \\times \\text{Equity multiplier}\\\\\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":200,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/8065e49dafe0cc478a61974197df97d8/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":102,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/8065e49dafe0cc478a61974197df97d8/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we can determine the debt-equity ratio, first we need to determine the equity multiplier. Since ROE is provided in the problem, we can already determine the equity multiplier.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{ROE}& =\n \\text{Profit Margin} \\times\\text{Asset Turnover} \\times \\text{Equity multiplier}\\\\\\\\\n15.84\\% &=6.4\\% \\times 1.77 \\times  \\text{Equity multiplier}  \\\\ \\\\\n0.1584 &=0.064 \\times 1.77 \\times  \\text{Equity multiplier}  \\\\ \\\\\n\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Since we are looking for the equity multiplier, we need to transfer ROE to the right side of the equation and the equity multiplier to the left side of the equation. The equation would look like this:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Equity multiplier}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{ROE}} {\\text{Profit Margin}\\times \\text{Asset Turnover}} \\\\ \\\\\n& = \\frac{15.84\\%} {6.4\\% \\times 1.77}\\\\ \\\\\n& = \\frac{0.1584} {0.064 \\times 1.77}\\\\ \\\\\n&= \\boxed{1.40}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\\\nAs can be seen, the equity multiplier is 1.40.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":603,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/7a06b8678f81bd2faa556cc9e9956d06/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":303,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/7a06b8678f81bd2faa556cc9e9956d06/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we proceed, let us first define debt-equity ratio.\n\n**Debt-equity ratio** compares a company's total debt to total equity and is determined by dividing the total liabilities by the total shareholders' equity.\n\nThe formula is denoted as follows:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Debt-equity ratio}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Total Liabilities}} {\\text{Total Shareholder's equity}}\\\\ \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":244,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/d1e02b45617e9d2d5088b80aeea36d79/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":123,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/d1e02b45617e9d2d5088b80aeea36d79/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Another way to determine the debt-equity ratio: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Debt-equity ratio}& = \\text{Equity multiplier - 1.00} \\\\ \\\\\n&=1.40 - 1.00\\\\ \\\\\n&=\\boxed{0.40}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\\\nIn conclusion, the debt-equity ratio is 0.40.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":337,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/873d138c3e7cc24fda65108736ea2c74/lateximg_large.png","width":806},"regular":{"height":170,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/873d138c3e7cc24fda65108736ea2c74/lateximg.png","width":403}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"0.40","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":22,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/e62d949e679c668e6f19d3f56c848672/lateximg_large.png","width":51},"regular":{"height":12,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/e8c899f1a66f171bce9b4d17d5d400cc/e62d949e679c668e6f19d3f56c848672/lateximg.png","width":27}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"d43720ce-eca4-404f-a636-94fd1a001c62","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880804,"exerciseName":"9","page":86,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"01fb5280-a40a-4566-ae36-f5e9102df78c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-questions-and-problems-9-01fb5280-a40a-4566-ae36-f5e9102df78c"},{"id":14880805,"exerciseName":"10","page":86,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"95c5aaef-0404-419d-a45c-981f853f3686","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-questions-and-problems-10-95c5aaef-0404-419d-a45c-981f853f3686"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880802,"exerciseName":"7","page":85,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"89363d91-ab61-4f07-a0fe-bb47a5a1bdc7","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-questions-and-problems-7-89363d91-ab61-4f07-a0fe-bb47a5a1bdc7"},{"id":14880801,"exerciseName":"6","page":85,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"bc027c55-c071-4e48-ae61-4c62705ae54a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-questions-and-problems-6-bc027c55-c071-4e48-ae61-4c62705ae54a"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-questions-and-problems-8-2c7bc9d4-8b5d-43b0-8c62-37d3bb4d9b74"}